Dokpesi was said to have been arrested on Sunday while travelling to the UK and would be arraigned today, Monday before a court. The police in the United Kingdom have reportedly arrested the Chairman of DAAR Communications Limited, High Chief Raymond Dokpesi. Dokpesi was said to have been arrested on Sunday while travelling to the UK and would be arraigned today, Monday before a court, according to The Whistler. Dokpesi, a chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Nigeria, was reportedly picked up at terminal 2 of Heathrow Airport in London on Sunday. He was said to have boarded a Lufthansa Flight LH916 from Frankfurt to London. “We were on a flight from Frankfurt to London and as we are about to arrive London, we were informed that we should all stay on our seat when the aircraft lands and that the police wanted to do something. We were informed that there will be a police operation. “So when we landed, the police came in and ask who is Raymond Dokpesi and they now took him away. He was wearing agbada. He was arrested in London,” a source who spoke to the newspaper said. Dokpesi, according to findings by this website would appear in court on Monday for remand.